ANTHONY: Nah, what's up, bro? You forgot me?

[Voices overlap]
ANTHONY: I died?
[Voices overlap]
DINO: You forgot me.
ANTHONY: Yeah, alright. Last time we talked you were playing basketball 'I'll call you
right back'... Friday. What are you doing? [Pause] You did the boilers? [Pause] You did the
boilers, bro?
DINO: Oh, yeah.
ANTHONY: Are you uh...? You start, you making a stop by over here, right? You're
gonna come by?
DINO: I'm not making do anything. So...
[Voices overlap]
ANTHONY: No, he said he is though. So [Stutters]...
[Voices overlap]
DINO: Alright.
ANTHONY: Alright.
DINO: Yeah, give him a big 'Thank you' when you see him.
ANTHONY: Of course I did. I gave him gas money.
DINO: Alright.
ANTHONY: Alright? Douchebag, [Stutters] you don't know what happened today. Paul
snapped out on Mom. On me and Mom.
DINO: Why?
ANTHONY: Because of his uh, because he didn't have her wine last night. So she woke
up, he's taking a shower. Ella had to come to go to the doctor with Mom at 1:00 o'clock, 1:00
o'clock. Ella was coming at 12:00. The doorbell rang once. So Mom said, 'Oh Paul, the
doorbell's ringing'. She was in the bathroom getting dressed. So the doorbell rang again, and
then she's like 'Cuz, someone get it'. She snapped out. Like 'Uh, [Stutters] you know it's Ella.
Well how come no one to get the door. I can't do everything'. And then once she came from the
doctor, he's like 'Oh, you know, [Stutters] I can't take it. I'm getting a little stressed out'. And Mom
has to stay downstairs with aunt Pat.
DINO: Oh my God.
ANTHONY: Yeah. My mother's hysterical crying, 'I don't want this one. I wanna go stay
with you'. I'm like 'No Ma, you can't go stay with us. He's up all night playing fucking video
games. You'll be up all night'. I just said that to shut her. You don't want my Mom staying with you,
bro.
[Voices overlap]
DINO: [Unintelligible]. Alright.
ANTHONY: No, no. Next Monday is the Inspection, bro.
DINO: Yup, got you. Alright. [Pause] Alright.
ANTHONY: You told... Alright.
DINO: I'm with him right now...
[End of Call]

[CROSS REFERENCE WITH WIRE CIII - 17 -2133 SESSION #7349 on TT5250

[Voices Overlap]
DINO: Show face?
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: Yeah, show face bro. Why'd you gotta put it all on my shoulders for? All this?
DINO: Put what on your shoulders? You're the one that is like, 'Oh... '
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: Dino, they don't want us here.
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: Got to know every detail like.
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: Yeah, because you gotta tell my cousin this because they don't want us
here. We are over here a month, bro.
DINO: They don't want you there. I know.
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: They don't. What? You don't know what happened? I didn't tell you what
happened Saturday, bro?
DINO: I know, [Mumbles]
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: My Aunt snapped out because she didn't have her pills. She snapped out
on everybody.
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: Well, you should have [Unintelligible].
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: No, yeah. [Stutters] Then she counted them wrong. She thought fucking I
took them. She counted wrong. The days were mixed up and she snapped out. 'I want to die.'
Screaming, fucking yelling at me. Fucking... forget it, bro. Just get me out of here, bro. Get my
mom in her apartment. Please.
DINO: I'm trying, dude.
ANTHONY: What do you mean, 'I'm trying dude.'? You don't even come here. Why
don't you come here for? You don't come here no more, at all.
DINO: For what?
ANTHONY: I don't know, for what? You can't come here?
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: Did you get that check or no? Did he give you the money?
ANTHONY: No, he's paying me off little-little.
DINO: But he's gotta to give you like 5-600 dollars [Unintelligible]
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: Who, Joe? No! I thought you meant... [Sighs] No, Joe is fucking [pause] He
was supposed to come today and pick me up.
DINO: That's [Unintelligible] money, you never called.
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: No, he said, what do you call it? He paid $600 dollars. I want to see the
receipt.
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: He told me $400.
ANTHONY: He told me 600. He told you 4?
DINO: Yeah, he told me 400.
ANTHONY: He told me 6. [Grunts.]
DINO: No, he told me 400 and that's the first payment.
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: Well, anyway, [Stutters] I don't think he's gonna make me pay for that
anyway so. He says we gotta meet up. But he didn't come today.
DINO: Well, that's my money.
ANTHONY: Whoa, whoa, whoa, relax bro. You didn't pay me a fucking penny back. So
what are you gonna do? Pay it all back at once? That's what you plan on doing?
DINO: No, that's not what I plan on doing. But if he gives you a 1,000 dollars dude,
that's 1,000 dollars off my bill.
ANTHONY: What do you mean 1,000 dollars off your bill?
DINO: He's gotta give me a Section 8 check for this month.
ANTHONY: Oh, he's giving you that for this month? He said that?
DINO: Yeah.
ANTHONY: Oh, so get it from him bro. What the fuck man?
DINO: No, I told him to give it to you.
ANTHONY: Give it to me?
DINO: Yeah. What's the difference?
ANTHONY: Because he ain't gonna fucking come here, bro. He's supposed to come
here today. Where is he? He said he was supposed to pick me up and we are gonna come over
to see you, he said. I called him up. He said he'll call you right back and he never called back
and he told me the fucking U-haul truck was 600 dollars.
DINO: No, he told me 4.
ANTHONY: He told me 600.
DINO: No, he told me 4.
ANTHONY: He told me 6 then I go, 'Joe, you know that money, man? I would never lie
to you bro. That I miscounted.' I said, 'There was 500 missing, bro. We were going to do
something about that, right?' He goes, 'Yeah, I'll pick you up.' When did he call me? Uh,
Saturday he called me. Oh you he called you up. Right after he called you and called me up. He
said, 'I just spoke to Dino, 'Blah, blah, blah, blah.' He said, 'The U-haul bill was 600.' I said,
'600?'
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: He told me 4.
ANTHONY: Yeah, I know. He just lied. That right there, he's a liar.
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: 600 for what?
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: That's what I said. I said, 'For what?' I said, 'The truck was only 3 days
late.' He goes, 'No, the mileage on it.' I said, 'The mileage? What we really did, drive from
Brooklyn to his house, and then I drove it to my Aunt's.'
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: And I told him it was going to be like 50 miles. That's not 50 miles.
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: Yeah, so 50 miles is only 200 dollars, bro. So say, 200 and 200... it should
be 400, like you said. 400. It should be around that.
DINO: That's what he said.
ANTHONY: He told me 6. So, I don't know. That means he's a liar. If he did that, if you
told you 4 and told me 6. Maybe he was just getting riled up to fucking, to get you fucking... what
you call? To make you look stupid. He's like, 'Oh, Dino, I don't know what he did with the truck. '
I got the bill. I got the what you call you call it? The notification. I'm like what the hell is this? He
actually paid it fucking like Friday or something. He waited that long, if anything maybe he got
late charges for not paying it. How the hell did he card anyway? [Pause] You there?
DINO: Yeah.
ANTHONY: Yeah, [Stammers] how did they put it? The only way we were all able to get
the truck, right?
DINO: Yep.
ANTHONY: Cause he put it on his card?
DINO: I guess so.
ANTHONY: I don't know. I thought we were going to get away with it. Alright, so what
he's doing? Putting up the thing tomorrow?
DINO: Yeah.
ANTHONY: [Stammers] I gotta ask the inspector, is there electricity in the house right
now?
DINO: Yeah.
ANTHONY: Because the other guy, when I talked to him Friday... He said, one of the
reasons why it could be... because he didn't know what was going on. He said the electricity has
to be turned on. You know what I mean? Leave it on until I get there and then we'll switch it over.
That's one of the thing, electricity and gas has to be working or else they'll fail it. The stove works
too?
DINO: Yeah.
ANTHONY: So that's all that has to be done right now, it's the stair case? It's the dent?
The Bannister?
DINO: Yeah, and the water heater.
ANTHONY: So, they said they did the water heater all this time.
DINO: Alright, don't worry about it. Bye.
ANTHONY: I'm not worried about it. Just fucking do everything for my mom, Dino.
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: I am. Just fucking in [Unintelligible] , bro.
ANTHONY: Yeah. [Chuckles]
[End of Call]

ANTHONY: My mother is gonna fucking die. Dino, you are gonna kill her.

[Voices Overlap]

ANTHONY: They are doing it as fast as they can do it?

ANTHONY: So what can me and you do to make it faster?

ANTHONY: We can't do the water heaters?
DINO: No, we can't!
ANTHONY: So when is it going to be done?
DINO: They are doing it bro?
ANTHONY: Tuesday?
DINO: Shit bro. I'm gonna kill her. Fuck you.
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: Yeah, bro. It's been a month. Are you kidding me?
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: It's not my fault.
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: It's not your fault? So what's going to happen? Tell me. What's going on
bro? When is it going to be finished? When is the banister going to be put up?
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: It's not my fault. You rushed out of there because you wanted that fucking
money. That's why you wanted to leave.
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: We had no choice. He wanted me out of there. What are you talking about?
They gave us another month.
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: Yeah, I know, you never go the fucking money.
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: Bro, that aint' the reason why. Dino, listen to me. When is the banister
going up?

DINO: That is the reason why. You could have been there another 5 - 6 months.

you talking about?
[Voices Overlap]

[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: Bro, my problems? Dino, this is your problem. We were supposed to be in
the house already. What are you talking about?
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: I paid for it. I paid for everything already.
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: So, why isn't it done? What are they doing? Why isn't it done?
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: [Unintelligible] Well, you should have given us the fucking money.
ANTHONY: Bro, when is it going to be done? Are we going to be in there this week?
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: Now, he got another job, now he's fucking pussy footing around
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: I'm asking you a question bro.
DINO: Yeah, I know.
ANTHONY: So, is it going to be done Tuesday, so the inspector can come?
DINO: Yeah, on Tuesday bro.
ANTHONY: Is the banister? We went down there, everything is done. They did the new
cement, they moved the line over. So what else? Just the banister and the boiler hooked up?
DINO: Yeah bro.
ANTHONY: Well listen, you know what else he said? You know the open window? He
said you gotta put plywood on those 2 open windows.
DINO: Yeah right.
ANTHONY: Do you remembering this? The 2 open windows are for plywood.
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: Yeah, I'm remembering. What do you think, I'm an idiot?
ANTHONY: They'll fail it. And you know that patch, that open thing, where you can see
the concrete on the other side? He said to put plywood on that too because they might say
something on that.
DINO: It's a separate address.
ANTHONY: Oh so it's a separate address. The smoke detectors? He called up to
make sure, the smoke detectors, the boilers and the back and that's it. Then it's done.
DINO: What do you mean? Smoke detector are in there.
ANTHONY: Yeah, I know that. That's what the Section 8 said. Make sure the Smoke
Detectors are in. The electricity. The gas is on, the water heater, the banister. He said those are
the most important things, then everything is fine.
DINO: Yeah, I know that. They are just making me fucking wait.
ANTHONY: So bro, you should let me know this bro.
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: I should have what?
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: Cause I would have got more money from him, bro. I would have got more
money to finish it.
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: [Unintelligible] all the fucking boilers dude.
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: I would have did the water heater, yeah. I would have done the gas lines.
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: You are gonna do it?
ANTHONY: So you are saying everything is gonna be done Tuesday?
DINO: Yeah, I hope so.
ANTHONY: So let me know so I can get the... I'll tell Joe.
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: Let you know? I paid this guy to do this already.
ANTHONY: You paid him to do it already? Wow.
DINO: The boilers are in. He piped out the boilers and everything.
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: Yeah, he didn't tie them in though. I saw them. I went down there. He didn't
tie them in. They are not tied in. They are there, they are put together, you know, they started.
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: [Unintelligible] was supposed to come in yesterday. I don't know why he
didn't come dude. I paid him to go up and do it.
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: I'm gotta be out of here before next Sunday.
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: I hear you dude.
ANTHONY: They are really gonna kick us out again. They actually said, 'You have to
leave.' Outright. Then they gave us... they said, 'You know what? We will give you another
week.' Then Aunt Pat came up today starting again. How come I didn't go over. How come I
didn't go to Dino? How come I didn't go Dino today, how come I didn't go yesterday. I said, 'I
went yesterday afternoon. What am I gonna go over there for? It's the same thing. It's not
finished.'
DINO: Fuck man.
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: My mom was crying all day. Hysterical crying all day. She doesn't want to
be here where she's not wanted. They gave us another week. They told me yesterday to go to
hotel. Then they thought about it and changed their minds. They out right kicked us out.

Participants: ANTHONY (IDed in Session ) [FORMERLY UM5250] DINO [Formerly UM8473/ id'ed in ses. 427] KOSIC aka DINO, Medin
Body:
DOLORES to DINO
DOLORES and DINO greet.
DOLORES: Listen, what's happening?
DINO: I'm just waiting to finish. I'm practically done, they just gotta tie the boilers
and that's it.
DOLORES: So listen, will it be finished tomorrow?
DINO: I think so.
DOLORES: Oh come on Dino. Don't you know if it's gonna be finished tomorrow?
DINO: They just have to come and tie the vents and the hot water and heaters and
boiler, that's it.
DOLORES: Can you call section 8 tomorrow?
DINO: Yeah, I can call section 8 tomorrow.
DOLORES: Please call them. Let them...if that's gonna be done, call them tomorrow.
This way they can come down maybe Friday and I can get the hell out of here.
DINO: Okay, I know.
DOLORES: You know?
DINO: I know. You know what it is?
DOLORES: What?
DINO: The guy who is doing all the work, he started another job and so he kinda
like left me hanging. So, I ran out of money. I didn't have no more money and we were waiting on
the... I was waiting on money ma'.
DOLORES: Alright, I understand.
DINO: That's all that it was. I was waiting on money, you know? These things are
not cheap.
DOLORES: Yes, I know it. I know it but... yeah...
DINO: You know so... Ma' I swear I'm working as fast as I can.
DOLORES and DINO continue to discuss how the repairs in the house is practically done.
DOLORES tells DINO to call section 8 tomorrow.
DOLORES: Tell them that you are going to rent to somebody else, that's it. That you
can't wait no more.
DINO: Okay, okay.
DOLORES: Okay Dino?
DINO: Yes ma'. Don't worry, you're gonna be in, in a couple of days.
DINO apologizes to his mom and tells her that there are some things that are out of his control.
He promises her she will be happy and will be out of the place she lives in no time.
[Call minimized off: 20:41:24 - 20:41:29]
[End of call]

Body:
DOLORES [Using Anthony's phone] to MEDIN a/k/a DINO
[Cross Reference Wire CIII 17 1948 Session 10437]
DINO: Hello? Hello?
DOLORES: Hi, Dino.
DINO: Hi Ma.
DOLORES: What are you doing?
DINO: Nah. I'm working.
DOLORES: Working?
DINO: Yeah.
DOLORES: Awww. You take time off to eat?
DINO No. Who got time for that, ma?
DOLORES: You haven't got time?!
DINO: Nah.
DOLORES: Well... you eat beef franfurters?
DINO: [Chuckles] Yeah.
DOLORES: I got beef frankfurters.
DINO: That's a'right, ma. You don't worry about nothing.
DOLORES: Ahhh. I got them. I got food here I'm taking.
DINO: I'm okay
DOLORES: A'right. Listen.
DINO: Hah?
[Voices Overlap]
DOLORES: They want me out of here at 6:00. So, I gotta come there at 6:00. Okay?
You could work. You know? You could work. I'm not gonna stop you.
DINO: Uh... Uh... Ask them if they could give you til like 7:00 or 8:00.
DOLORES: They won't give me it. They told me 6:00.
DINO: A'ight. A'ight. No problem.
DOLORES: I just don't wanna curse on the phone.
DINO: That's okay.
DOLORES: I'm gonna get there in a car service. Okay?
DINO: Okay Where's Anthony?
DOLORES: He's putting the stuff in... my food in the bag.
DINO: A'ight. You got it.
[Voices Overlap]
DOLORES: Okay. I'll see you later, babe.
DINO: A'right.
DOLORES: Bye
DINO: Bye
[End of Call]
